# business-documents / python-barcode

Generate standard 1D barcodes (EAN, UPC, Code128, Code39, ITF, ISBN, Codabar, …) as deterministic, dependency-free SVG using the pure-Python `python-barcode` library. SVG is the default writer: pure text, diffable, version-controllable, zero binary/font dependencies. Raster PNG is available via the optional Pillow ImageWriter.

controls do
  business-documents.data: { label: "Barcode data", type: "text" }
  business-documents.type: { label: "Barcode type", type: "select", options: ["ean13", "ean8", "upca", "code128", "code39", "isbn13", "itf", "codabar"] }
  business-documents.module_height: { label: "Module height (mm)", type: "range" }
  business-documents.write_text: { label: "Render human-readable text", type: "toggle" }
end

## Required reading
- python-barcode docs (project, no usage restriction): https://python-barcode.readthedocs.io/
- Source / API (MIT): https://github.com/Whic/python-barcode
- No official Anthropic/Claude skill and no notable community skill exists (as of 2026-06); author directly against the upstream docs.

## Render
```bash
# SVG only (zero deps):
pip install "python-barcode==0.16.1"
# For PNG/raster add Pillow:
# pip install "python-barcode[images]==0.16.1"
bash tools/steps/business-documents-python-barcode.sh "$SESSION" "$OUT"
```

## Failure modes
- `save()` appends the extension automatically — pass the path WITHOUT an extension or you get e.g. `out.svg.svg`.
- EAN/UPC require an exact-length numeric data string; the writer auto-computes the trailing check digit, so supply data WITHOUT the final check digit.
- PNG/raster output needs the `[images]` extra (Pillow) and `writer=ImageWriter()`; SVGWriter cannot emit PNG.
- Pin version 0.16.1: glyph/font rendering of the human-readable text varies across releases, breaking deterministic diffs.
- Code128/Code39 accept alphanumeric data; numeric-only types (EAN/UPC/ITF) reject letters.
